1. To build emacs from source first install its build dependencies
sudo apt install build-essential
sudo apt build-dep emacs 

2. Download emacs source code from
http://ftp.gnu.org/gnu/emacs/

3. Extract archive and cd to source code folder

4. Run
./configure
Look at output if there are any errors. If they are find missing dependencies and install it manualy

5. Run
make

Run binary from source_dir_name/src/emacs

If emacs works install it

6. Run 
sudo make install
